# Agent & LLM Instructions ΓÇö Principles of Excellent Software (Tauri v2 + Svelte 5 desktop suite)

> **Purpose.** This file is the single, canonical "manual of good software" for this workspace.
> It encodes every pattern that is already **standard, consolidated and battle-tested** across the
> apps so that an agentic LLM can **replicate a new desktop application end-to-end, fast and consistently**:
> the banded shell + sidebar, dark/light theming, 15-language i18n, the toast/dialog/shortcut systems,
> the Whisper integration (including the real build fix), and the full Git + AUR release pipeline with all
> its safety checks.
>
> **This exact file is copied identically** into every project (`reaper`, `vesta`, `textmerger`,
> `effywhisper`, and the workspace root). Project-specific values (palette, Vite port, CSS framework)
> live in the clearly-labelled per-project sub-sections ΓÇö read the one that matches the repo you are in.
>
> **How to use it.** Treat every rule below as a hard requirement unless the user explicitly overrides it.
> When in doubt, mirror the most mature reference implementation: **`reaper` and `vesta`** are the gold
> standard for layout, Whisper, and the release scripts; `textmerger` is the gold standard for the simpler
> single-crate structure. Prefer *reusing* an existing consolidated solution over inventing a new one.

---

## 0. Golden Rules (read first)

1. **Never hardcode colors.** Every color comes from a semantic CSS variable (`--bg`, `--surface`, `--accent`, ΓÇª). See ┬º2.
2. **No raw browser defaults.** No native `<select>`, `<input type=checkbox>`, default scrollbars, or default focus outlines in the app UI. See ┬º5.
3. **One source of truth per concern.** Version ΓåÆ `PKGBUILD` `pkgver`. Heavy logic ΓåÆ a shared crate in `lib/`. Translations ΓåÆ `en.json` (master) + per-language overrides.
4. **Don't duplicate heavy logic across apps.** Extract it into a decoupled, callback-driven Rust crate (┬º12, ┬º13).
5. **Every change is logged.** Append a dated technical entry to `docs/list_of_things_changed.md` as you edit source.
6. **Validate before declaring done.** `cargo check` (not full build) for Rust; run the i18n audit; for a release, run the full pipeline in ┬º15.
7. **Return whole files when you modify code/scripts.** Never hand back fragments of a script the user has to splice in.
8. **Accessibility and RTL are not optional.** Keyboard handlers on every custom control; logical CSS properties everywhere (┬º5.12).

